The paper proposes a machine learning approach for unsupervised domain adaptation, which is a common problem in natural language processing and computer vision. The paper specifically focuses on sentiment analysis and part-of-speech tagging, which are subfields of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV), respectively. The proposed approach involves a mixture-of-experts model, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the issue of negative transfer, which is a concern in transfer learning (cs.SD). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.SD, in that order.
